# Transp. Code
## Title 7
### Chapter 723. Tex. Traffic Safety Act
##### § 723.012 — Traffic Safety Program

The statewide traffic safety program must include:

    (1) a driver education and training program administered by the governor through appropriate agencies that complies with Section 723.013 (Driver Education and Training Program) ;

    (2) plans for improving:

        (A) driver licensing;

        (B) collision records;

        (C) vehicle inspection, registration, and titling;

        (D) traffic engineering;

        (E) personnel;

        (F) police traffic supervision;

        (G) traffic courts;

        (H) highway design; and

        (I) uniform traffic laws; and

    (3) plans for local traffic safety programs by legal and political subdivisions of this state that may be implemented if the programs:

        (A) are approved by the governor; and

        (B) conform with uniform standards adopted under the Highway Safety Act of 1966 (23 U.S.C. Sec. 401 et seq.).

*Acts 2023, 88th Leg., R.S., Ch. 709 (H.B.2190), Sec. 103, eff. September 1, 2023.*
